Solutions for SQL Functions Section

SELECT
  borough,
  COUNT(*)
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.new_york.nypd_mv_collisions`
WHERE
  TIMESTAMP_DIFF(CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), timestamp, DAY) <= 365
GROUP BY
  borough
SELECT
  EXTRACT(year FROM created_at) AS created_at_year,
  CONCAT(status,'-','health') AS status_health,
  curb_loc,
  COUNT(DISTINCT tree_id ) AS cnt
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.new_york.tree_census_2015`
GROUP BY
  status_health,
  curb_loc,
  created_at_year
SELECT
  DISTINCT name
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.usa_names.usa_1910_current`
WHERE
  SUBSTR(LOWER(name),1,1) = SUBSTR(LOWER(name),-1,1)
ORDER BY
  name DESC
SELECT
  AVG(trip_total/100) AS avg_trip_total_dollars
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.chicago_taxi_trips.taxi_trips`
SELECT
  STDDEV_POP(trip_total/100) AS standard_deviation_trip_total_dollars
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.chicago_taxi_trips.taxi_trips`

Query:

SELECT
  ROUND(trip_total/100,1) AS trip_total_dollars,
  COUNT(DISTINCT unique_key) AS num_trips
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.chicago_taxi_trips.taxi_trips`
GROUP BY
  trip_total_dollars

Distribution:

SELECT
  CAST(start_date AS date) AS date,
  AVG(TIMESTAMP_DIFF(end_date, start_date, MINUTE)) AS avg_trip_duration_minutes,
  SUM(TIMESTAMP_DIFF(end_date, start_date, MINUTE)) AS total_minutes,
  COUNT(*) AS num_trips
FROM
  `bigquery-public-data.london_bicycles.cycle_hire`
GROUP BY
  date
ORDER BY
  date ASC
